If you are using distro with package system you can install this program from
your repository, if it is available. If it's not or your distro has no package
system â€” follow the next steps:

1. Install Qt4 dependencies. There are qt-core and qt-gui packages in the
Gentoo distro, for example.

2. Install C++ compiler from GNU Compilers Collection (gcc).

3. Open terminal emulator, change current directory to this, where the README
file is and type the next commands:

./configure
make
sudo cp qfontviewer /usr/local/bin

4. To run the program just type

qfontviewer
